  "body": "the new hyperkube image has **changed** without notifying the bash environment now links to sh,\r\nthere is only one  thing worst than an error, and it is a **SILENT ERROR**\r\nthis means that anyone that execute kubectl inside the hyperkube and leverage from a bash environment now get the weirdest exceptions , in my case troubles where caused by flexvolume scripted in bash which stopped working without reason and with weird errors logged ( but also there are some other cluster-images based on your hyperkube image, and if you link bash to sh it will spread headache around :) )\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nroot@v:~# docker run --rm -ti gcr.io/google_containers/hyperkube:v1.8.2 bash\r\n# echo hello\r\nhello\r\n# echo -e hello\r\n-e hello\r\n# which bash\r\n/bin/bash\r\n# bash\r\n# bash --version\r\nbash: 0: Illegal option --\r\n# ls -la /bin/bash\r\nlrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 7 Sep  1 23:58 /bin/bash -> /bin/sh\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nwhile for version 1.7.7 the result was different\r\n```bash\r\nroot@v:~# docker run --rm -ti gcr.io/google_containers/hyperkube:v1.7.7 bash                                                                                                                                                             \r\nroot@1fb7ff758919:/# bash --version\r\nGNU bash, version 4.3.30(1)-release (x86_64-pc-linux-gnu)\r\nCopyright (C) 2013 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\r\nLicense GPLv3+: GNU GPL version 3 or later <http://gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html>\r\n\r\nThis is free software; you are free to change and redistribute it.\r\nThere is NO WARRANTY, to the extent permitted by law.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nso , or remove bash, or repristinate bash,\r\nlink bash->sh is a NO-NO \r\n",
